result.name: Hong Kong Delights

reviews.text: Not much of options but good for quick bites

A lovely place to relax for a meal. Fairly cheap, too.

From their website: "Hong Kong Delights brings together the true essence of Chinese and Western food cultures. Its warm and colourful décor offers a fresh and vibrant retro atmosphere with 60’s and 70’s imagery. The restaurant offers an array of classic dishes, each of which embraces the very essence of Chinese and Western cuisine."

Spent 4 days in Hong Kong 
Took the ferry to Macau 
The casinos are amazing
Pineapple bun with butter is normal taste, not special but french toast is greasy.
One of the best meals I've had in HongKong . .lots of variety on menu for traditional local food with reasonable price. Highly recommended
